Mary Sellers https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_Sellers 0 Wanja Mary Sellers (born September 3, 1962) is an American actress and director. She became known in the second half of the 1980s for starring in numerous Italian horror films such as Stage Fright (1987), Ghosthouse (1988) and Demons 5 (1989). Born in Nairobi, Kenya, she later relocated to Rome, Italy and pursued an acting career. She made her screen debut in Fabrizio Laurenti's short film, The Immigrant (1985).
